# IUUT — .gitignore
# Governance: .agent/SECURITY_PROTOCOL.md prohibits committed PII; .agent/CODE_STYLE.md §12
# pins the standard ignores below.

# .NET build outputs
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Oo]ut/
[Ll]og/
[Ll]ogs/

# Release artifacts (published single-file exe + zip + checksums; reproduce via scripts/publish-release.ps1)
[Aa]rtifacts/

# Visual Studio / Rider / VS Code user-specific
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# Test outputs
[Tt]est[Rr]esults/
*.trx
*.coverage
*.coveragexml

# NuGet
*.nupkg
*.snupkg
.nuget/

# Local IUUT scratch
*.iuut-backup-*
*.iuut-tmp-*

# IUUT user-state files that must NEVER be committed (PII risk per SECURITY_PROTOCOL §2)
*steam-api-key*
*.steam-credentials
*loginusers.vdf

# OS junk
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
desktop.ini

# Local environment overrides (not committed)
*.local.json
appsettings.Development.json

# Coverage / profiling
*.profdata
coverage*.json
coverage*.xml
BenchmarkDotNet.Artifacts/

# Compiled binaries / debug symbols — NEVER committed (shipped exe is built by publish-release.ps1).
# The repo is source-only; the only large things that exist are build outputs (already ignored above).
*.exe
*.dll
*.pdb
*.so
*.dylib

# Archives + game data assets — keep the 36 GB paks / 72 MB exe / data.pak dumps out of git.
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar
*.pak
*.ucas
*.utoc
*.usmap
*.dat
oo2core*.dll
# data.pak re-mine dumps (scripts/extract-datapak.ps1 writes under artifacts/, already ignored)
datapak/

# More IDE / build tooling
*.code-workspace
*.sln.iml
_ReSharper*/
*.DotSettings.user
.fleet/
*.binlog
*.tlog
project.lock.json
[Pp]ublish/

# Patch / merge / temp junk
*.orig
*.rej
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log
